-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----
pbpaste | python3 -c " import sys, textwrap raw =
sys.stdin.read().strip() raw =
raw.replace('','').replace('','').strip() wrapped =
textwrap.fill(raw, 64) pem = '\n' + wrapped + '\n' with
open('kalshi_key.pem', 'w') as f:     f.write(pem)
print('kalshi_key.pem created successfully') " ```  `pbpaste`
reads from your clipboard on Mac. So: 1. Copy contents of `QZN
KALSHI BOT.txt` 2. Run that command 3. It creates
`kalshi_key.pem` in your `kalshi-flywheel` folder  Then in
Railway set: ``` KALSHI_PRIVATE_KEY=kalshi_key.pem
-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----